headline.print_headline: Slowdown at U.S. Port of Tacoma Threatens Christmas Tree Shipments to Asia
headline.main: Slowdown at U.S. Port of Tacoma Threatens Christmas Tree Shipments to Asia

lead_paragraph: A slowdown at a busy Washington state port amid a labor dispute could mean that thousands of Christmas trees grown in the Pacific Northwest will not be shipped in time to meet holiday demand in Asia, industry officials said on Monday.
